 vastness of the region and limited previous overviews, this volume focuses on an account of the families and major languages of each area within the region, including brief grammatical descriptions of many of the languages. The volume also includes a typological overview of Papuan languages, and a chapter on Austronesian-Papuan contact. It will make accessible current knowledge on this complex region, and will be the standard reference on the region. It is aimed at typologists, endangered language specialists, graduate and advanced undergraduate students, and all those interested in linguistic diversity and understanding this least known linguistic region.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aLanguage and culturezPapua New Guinea. 0aPapuan languages. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh  aPapuan Languages, Linguistic Typology, Language Contact.1 aArka, Wayan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarroll, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChoi, Yun Jung, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDunn, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDöhler, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Bethwyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFoley, William A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGast, Volker, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHammarström, Harald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolton, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKashima, Eri, eco